BUS: PROTO: The Ombudsman

Swann wrote:

>PROTO: The Ombudsman

<snip>

>     In order to be eligible to be the Ombudsman, the following must be 
>     true of a Player;

>       i) The Player must hold no Office or be the Speaker.

I think you mean "nor be the Speaker".  As it reads, the Speaker can be the
Ombudsman, even if e holds other Offices.

<snip> (I really like the idea of collecting and reporting grievances)

>Let the following rule be crated;
>(Title: Special Privileges of the Ombudsman)

>     The Ombudsman shall have the following rights and privileges, to be 
>     exercised only in the spirit of advocacy for *all* Agorans;

>       i) Once every month, the Ombudsman is permitted and empowered to 
>          vacate all the Blots on a single individual Player.  This must 
>          only be done to correct what the Ombudsman believes to be an 
>          injustice to an otherwise Rule-abiding Player.

This will upset the "Hot Blot" mechanism temporarily, but since that is now
self-correcting (to some extent) I don't see this as a show-stopper.

>      ii) The Ombudsman is permitted to cast an additional two votes 
>          AGAINST any proposal e believes disenfranchises a large number 
>          of Players,  distributes power unfairly, or adversely affects 
>          a large class of Players who do not themselves have the 
>          resources to oppose.

>     iii) The Ombudsman has the power to, once a week, pay out one of 
>          any currency minted by the Bank to any single Player who has 
>          none of that currency.

Same here, if the Ombudsman pays out an Indulgence.  It would be more
controversial and subject the Ombudsman to possible negative political
feedback, but it might be interesting in i) and iii) to allow the Ombudsman, in
the case of Indulgences, to issue Payment Orders from one Player to another
rather than let em vacate Blots or pay out from the Bank.

<snip>

Interesting idea, with I lot of potential, I think.

-- Crito


